  "doc_id": "19337",
  "text": "The International Society of Neuropathology-Haarlem consensus guidelines for nervous system tumor classification and grading recommends grade evaluation before molecular analysis [CITATION_1] . Thus, from the expression levels of the 92 genes, a subset of genes able to discriminate between WHO grades was selected on the basis of 2 statistical analyses: (i) Genes showing a significant difference between grade II, III and IV tumors by t-test (p < 0.05); and (ii) genes highly correlated with grade II, III or IV tumors. Principal component analysis (PCA) was performed with the FactoMineR package [CITATION_2] and hierarchical clustering (HC) with the ComplexHeatmap package [CITATION_3] .",
